India’s 10-Year Bond Yields Rise to 8.52%, Highest in 3 Years

-- B y   A n i l   V a r m a
-- 
2011-10-03T04:54:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/india-s-10-year-bond-yields-rise-to-8-52-highest-in-3-years.html
India ’s 10-year bonds fell for a
fifth day, pushing yields to the highest level in three years,
after the government increased by 32 percent its scheduled debt
sales for the six months ending March 31.  The yield on the 7.8 percent note due April 2021 jumped
eight basis points to 8.52 percent, the highest level since
September 2008, according to the central bank’s trading system.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anil Varma at 
 avarma3@bloomberg.net  